==English==

====Homophones====
*[[palate]] (''possibly depending on dialect or accent'')
*[[pallet]]
*[[pallette]]

===Etymology===
From French, from Old French ''palette'', diminutive of ''pale'', from the Latin ''pala''.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ælɪt|-ælɪt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A thin [[board]] on which a [[painter]] lays and mixes [[colour]]s.
# The [[range]] of colors in a given [[work]] or item or body of work. 

